records.addlTxt:
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  

The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 7 MONTHS at the House of Corrections with 2 days credit CONSECUTIVE to any other sentence.

Court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on 1 YEAR probation.

  Conditions of Probation:
- Successfully complete an anger management class and follow through with counseling if deemed appropriate by the department.
- Obtain/maintain fulltime employment/education/vocation.
- No contact with: Nicholas G.
- Follow all rules of supervision and follow through with any other treatment deemed necessary by the department.

Court ordered the defendant pay all of the following by the end of supervision.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment:
Restitution in the amount of $463.48 payable to Crime Victim Compensation and $1377 payable to Nicholas G; 
All court costs, fees, and surcharges (including DNA); 
All applicable fees of supervision.
-  No Cash Bail Posted in this matter 

Upon successful completion of the sentence, including restitution paid in FULL,  Court will consider motion for expungement.

Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.
